		"description": "<p>Also at 3rd level, so long as you have 10 minutes and access to @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.d8aj2xoatccd71ce]{Alchemist's Supplies} you may craft an alchemical balm that may help abate your frenzied state. This balm has no effect on other creatures and may be crafted as part of a short or long rest. You may craft a number of these balms equal to half of your proficiency bonus (rounded down), though if they go unused they spoil within 24 hours.</p><p>When you would be forced to make your saving throw to resist your @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.Zy5SjEocWsJaxdiy]{Blood Frenzy}, you may use your reaction to immediately apply the balm, granting you an expertise die to the roll for a number of rounds equal to your Intelligence modifier.</p><p>Your expertise die to this save increases to a d6 at 10th level and a d8 at 17th level. This expertise die cannot be increased by any other feature or spell.</p>",
